	Americans have  generally been reluctant to recongize this, quickly dismissing suggestions that Soviet cultivation may play a crucial though of course not total role in the growth of international terrorism and domestic discord in Western societies. This reluctance is understandable, since conspiracy is alien to the American experience while red-baiting demagogy is not.
